The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their application to real-world problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on learning a reward function from interaction with the user and optimizing it with reinforcement learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The agent alignment problem and the discussion of ways to establish trust in the resulting agents suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the mention of optimizing the learned reward function in complex and general domains suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
